      "body": "It's still imprecise as of master @ 4c1090c882ea15ba4d10a2f7f320f3c0eb490ebd.\r\n\r\nAn alternative way to create a blockchain snapshot is to call `invalidateblock` on the next height. This approach is used in #16899. I don't think that's an ideal solution though; if there's forks you have to invalidate all of them, and if you don't shutdown p2p it starts disconnecting peers. So I'd prefer a more robust RPC call for this purpose like `rollbacktoheight`, which also requires fixing this precision issue. ",
